{
  "texts": [
    "GRACE/GRACE-FO products are provided after various processing algorithms, for example, the level 2 (L2) products are available in terms of the spherical harmonics potential coefficients.",
    "These timevariable fields, after a proper filtering (e.g., [62], [63]) and, destripping, geophysical corrections via forward modeling (glacial isostatic adjustment, geocenter, ellipsoidal corrections) (e.g., [64]) can be used to estimate level 3 (L3) TWS.",
    "Alternatively, mascon solutions are also available that provide GRACE data as regularized gridded TWS estimates [65], [66], [67].Various studies have demonstrated the connection between the long-term trends or changes in the amplitude of seasonal (net) precipitation and TWS.",
    "Since GRACE TWS reflects both climate change and anthropogenic modifications impacts, it has an invaluable contribution in monitoring the water storage decline (mainly in groundwater) in transboundary river basins [68].",
    "GRACE/GRACE-FO data are being used to study hydrological droughts."
  ]
}